childnodes.sy: If you haven’t been to Dick’s, you haven’t been to Seattle. This classic spot serves great cheeseburgers, fries and shakes. Make sure to separate your compost from your recyclables when you’re all done.

Whether you’re looking for a tasty brunch, a good date spot or late-night drinks, the versatile Café Pettirosso has you covered. Brunch offerings include a little something for everyone, like the tofu scramble, French toast or cheese & egg sandwich.

It started out as one of Seattle’s favorite food trucks, and now Marination has a great waterside location. Tacos and the kimchi rice bowl are customer favorites, but don’t miss out on the Spam slider with nunya sauce.

Tacos Chukis in the Capitol Hill neighborhood is quick, easy, tasty and inexpensive — what else could you ask for? Grab a couple of friends so you can try it all: the house tacos, baby burritos, pork quesadilla and chicken tamales.

A big, hot bowl of San Fernando’s chicken noodle soup is perfect on a chilly night in Seattle, and their succulent roasted Peruvian chicken is a treat in any kind of weather. Check out the banquet room in the back if you need to host a big event.
Café Turko may be best known for dinner, but their little-known weekend breakfast service includes tasty dishes and drinks like stellar omelets and sour cherry juice.

Enjoy Sunday at Sun Ya, where they serve up some of the dim sum in town. The Chinese broccoli, duck, and pork and shrimp dumplings are all delicious, but also very filling, so bring a friend along to share.
